<h1><img src="new.gif">
d67 1
a67 25

<br clear="both"><hr>
<h1>TopGun WingMan: WWW Browser for Palm Pilot</h1>

In addition to scalable Internet proxy service, our other <a
href="#prevwork">prior work</a> concentrates on how to enable
Internet applications for "thin" clients.  Our philosophy is: keep the
client simple, and put intelligence in the infrastructure.  We are
bringing this philosophy to bear on the Palm Pilot by producing a
graphical WWW browser, building on prior work by the
<a href="http://www.isaac.cs.berkeley.edu">UC Berkeley ISAAC Group</a>.
TopGun
WingMan will exploit TranSend via GLAP (the GloMop Lightweight
Application Protocol), which makes its code smaller and produces a
faster Web surfing experience than commercial
browsers.<p>

We expect to make TopGun WingMan freely available when it is ready,
initially in binary and then in source form.
Watch this space for details.  In the meantime, you can get other TopGun
software for the Pilot <a
href="http://www.isaac.cs.berkeley.edu/pilot/">here,</a> including
Telnet with terminal emulation, ssh, and SSLeay.


